If the text:
9       plum (9, seven spaces, plum)
is processed with "unexpand -a -t 2", the computed tab stops are denoted with
a "T" below:

1 9
2
3 T
4
5 T
6
7 T
8
9 p T
10 l
11 u T
12 m

Therefore, the text is converted to:

9\t\t\t\tplum (9, four tabs, plum)

With corresponding character positions after each tab as follows:
\t: 3
\t: 5
\t: 7
\t: 9
